1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,000
https://slama.dev/comeback/

2
00:00:10,950 --> 00:00:13,150
Oh, damn it again.

3
00:00:21,280 --> 00:00:21,880
Gross.

4
00:00:23,150 --> 00:00:24,330
Sorry, Mr. Pacovsky.

5
00:00:24,550 --> 00:00:25,210
What's going on?

6
00:00:25,450 --> 00:00:26,950
We have a delivery, this.

7
00:00:27,650 --> 00:00:28,350
What is it?

8
00:00:28,550 --> 00:00:30,050
There's a letter inside.

9
00:00:33,950 --> 00:00:39,750
Tomas, if you're reading this letter, it means I'm dead.

10
00:00:40,850 --> 00:00:43,550
Pay my debts and adopt the kids.

11
00:00:44,650 --> 00:00:47,950
If the body is in one piece, coffin, otherwise cremate.

12
00:00:48,650 --> 00:00:49,550
Thanks, Simona.

13
00:00:54,550 --> 00:00:57,750
Lexa, nothing happened to your mom, it's just a precaution.

14
00:00:58,190 --> 00:00:58,710
Oh right.

15
00:00:58,850 --> 00:01:00,270
The blue one then.

16
00:01:04,150 --> 00:01:16,250
Tomas, if you're reading this letter, it means either A, I'm in the hospital, B, at a spa, C, I found someone, D, I've been kidnapped.

17
00:01:17,350 --> 00:01:19,850
Start saving and watch the kids.

18
00:01:21,450 --> 00:01:24,580
If I don't come back within a week, open the red letter.

19
00:01:24,580 --> 00:01:25,460
Thanks, Simona.

20
00:01:29,250 --> 00:01:30,050
Nothing else?

21
00:01:30,950 --> 00:01:33,750
We were also supposed to say, cross out what doesn't apply.

22
00:02:14,360 --> 00:02:14,740
Hey.

23
00:02:14,780 --> 00:02:15,220
Hi.

24
00:02:15,220 --> 00:02:15,680
Hey.

25
00:02:16,950 --> 00:02:17,650
Simona's disappeared.

26
00:02:18,050 --> 00:02:18,740
I'm going to look for her.

27
00:02:18,740 --> 00:02:19,220
Where?

28
00:02:19,500 --> 00:02:19,980
No idea.

29
00:02:20,550 --> 00:02:21,950
Probably the hospital or Marianky spa.

30
00:02:22,920 --> 00:02:24,880
We think more likely the hospital.

31
00:02:25,020 --> 00:02:28,100
Because she left on her bike cursing about a stomachache.

32
00:02:28,340 --> 00:02:30,460
When she goes to the spa, she usually whistles.

33
00:02:31,340 --> 00:02:32,640
Which hospital is closest?

34
00:02:32,820 --> 00:02:33,940
The Sisters of No Mercy.

35
00:02:34,400 --> 00:02:35,460
I'll try there.

36
00:02:35,660 --> 00:02:37,840
Wait, that means Simona isn't at the pub?

37
00:02:38,020 --> 00:02:38,780
Apparently not.

38
00:02:39,350 --> 00:02:41,360
But Ozzak has his Saint Patrick's run today.

39
00:02:41,750 --> 00:02:43,400
What on earth is that?

40
00:02:43,450 --> 00:02:46,640
Eat a kilo of hot peppers at once and then run to Simona's to wash it down.

41
00:02:46,950 --> 00:02:50,780
He'll run somewhere else then. The nearest place is Strunc's and that's two kilometers.

42
00:02:50,780 --> 00:03:03,820
That was fast.

43
00:03:04,350 --> 00:03:06,250
Yeah, Simona's place is closed.

44
00:03:06,450 --> 00:03:07,650
Simona disappeared.

45
00:03:07,820 --> 00:03:08,740
Well, alright then.

46
00:03:09,350 --> 00:03:10,250
I'm off.

47
00:03:13,150 --> 00:03:16,050
Ivuska, for water, this is actually pretty good.

48
00:03:16,550 --> 00:03:17,880
It's tap water.

49
00:03:17,880 --> 00:03:18,320
Yeah.

50
00:03:19,650 --> 00:03:20,650
Buy it more often then.

51
00:03:26,850 --> 00:03:29,050
She's the only patient who's ever arrived by bike.

52
00:03:29,850 --> 00:03:31,780
She had acute appendicitis.

53
00:03:31,780 --> 00:03:32,380
Hi, Tomas.

54
00:03:32,920 --> 00:03:34,360
I'm glad I found you.

55
00:03:34,560 --> 00:03:35,960
I'll leave you two.

56
00:03:36,020 --> 00:03:37,040
But keep an eye on her.

57
00:03:37,380 --> 00:03:40,600
The appendix is already out, but after this anesthesia there can be seizures.

58
00:03:41,850 --> 00:03:45,650
But don't worry, it happens very rarely.

59
00:03:48,580 --> 00:03:53,560
Simona, for God's sake, what happened to you?

60
00:03:53,560 --> 00:03:58,350
Oh please, I felt sick all morning, like when I was expecting the twins, so I went to the gynecologist just in case.

61
00:03:58,750 --> 00:04:01,080
And thank God, it was just the appendix.

62
00:04:01,080 --> 00:04:02,000
Did you get the letters?

63
00:04:02,080 --> 00:04:03,000
Yeah, yeah, yeah.

64
00:04:03,020 --> 00:04:03,340
Great.

65
00:04:03,540 --> 00:04:05,440
And don't forget to always check Sasa's pockets.

66
00:04:05,460 --> 00:04:06,440
She brings bugs home.

67
00:04:06,980 --> 00:04:07,480
What?

68
00:04:07,740 --> 00:04:09,520
She keeps wanting a pet.

69
00:04:09,520 --> 00:04:13,300
Lexa wants a daddy, so he brings home homeless people, but those you can't miss.

70
00:04:13,450 --> 00:04:17,050
Oh, and tell Ozzak that starting tomorrow Horvat will watch the pub.

71
00:04:17,650 --> 00:04:19,250
Don't worry, we'll manage somehow.

72
00:04:19,250 --> 00:04:20,740
How long will you be here?

73
00:04:20,850 --> 00:04:23,340
They promised if there are no complications, up to two weeks.

74
00:04:23,340 --> 00:04:24,700
Let's hope there won't be any.

75
00:04:25,240 --> 00:04:25,740
Don't complain.

76
00:04:26,350 --> 00:04:27,970
It's like a holiday here.

77
00:04:28,250 --> 00:04:32,030
You just lie around, food brought to your bed, all the tea you want, and all for free.

78
00:04:32,030 --> 00:04:33,610
I wouldn't say free.

79
00:04:33,610 --> 00:04:35,710
You know how much you pay those thieving insurance companies?

80
00:04:35,850 --> 00:04:36,090
Oh come on.

81
00:04:36,650 --> 00:04:40,250
And Miss Iva, if you need anything, just ring.

82
00:04:40,250 --> 00:04:40,770
Thank you.

83
00:04:43,860 --> 00:04:45,040
What do you mean, Miss Iva?

84
00:04:45,040 --> 00:04:46,950
She must have mistaken me for someone.

85
00:04:53,440 --> 00:04:53,960
What?

86
00:04:54,280 --> 00:04:54,920
Calm down.

87
00:04:55,750 --> 00:04:57,280
How am I supposed to calm down?

88
00:04:57,350 --> 00:05:00,860
You said yourself those insurance companies are terrible crooks, and Iva's covered by the state.

89
00:05:01,250 --> 00:05:02,450
Don't get upset.

90
00:05:02,480 --> 00:05:03,860
And Sasa isn't covered by the state?

91
00:05:04,080 --> 00:05:05,980
I registered Sasa as a guide dog.

92
00:05:06,020 --> 00:05:07,680
You get bigger subsidies for a dog than for a child.

93
00:05:08,020 --> 00:05:10,080
You want them to lock me up at the vet?

94
00:05:10,340 --> 00:05:11,980
Are you making fun of the state?

95
00:05:12,060 --> 00:05:13,820
I figured you wouldn't understand.

96
00:05:14,140 --> 00:05:15,580
I certainly don't.

97
00:05:15,700 --> 00:05:17,100
And brace yourself for the burger.

98
00:05:19,300 --> 00:05:19,700
Stop faking.

99
00:05:24,450 --> 00:05:25,450
Everyone get out.

100
00:05:27,810 --> 00:05:29,570
That fraud is faking it.

101
00:05:29,950 --> 00:05:30,350
Out!

102
00:05:31,450 --> 00:05:33,350
Dad, I can handle it.

103
00:05:34,850 --> 00:05:36,060
I'll call the doctor.

104
00:05:36,060 --> 00:05:38,150
There, it's passed.

105
00:05:42,250 --> 00:05:44,250
What are you doing here?

106
00:05:58,790 --> 00:05:59,430
I sleep here.

107
00:05:59,490 --> 00:06:00,010
Hold on.

108
00:06:01,900 --> 00:06:03,300
Come back, I'll catch them.

109
00:06:03,300 --> 00:06:05,520
Yeah right, the apartment is full of them.

110
00:06:05,750 --> 00:06:06,850
What's going on?

111
00:06:06,920 --> 00:06:07,980
My bed bugs escaped.

112
00:06:08,360 --> 00:06:09,280
Let them be.

113
00:06:10,350 --> 00:06:11,520
No way, one crawled into my ear.

114
00:06:11,520 --> 00:06:11,980
What?

115
00:06:12,750 --> 00:06:15,300
I just wanted a pet until Mom comes back.

116
00:06:15,300 --> 00:06:17,140
And I got a few extras just in case.

117
00:06:17,720 --> 00:06:19,280
Idiot, I brought you a spider.

118
00:06:19,520 --> 00:06:20,620
Ew, a spider.

119
00:06:22,550 --> 00:06:25,540
What's going on here?

120
00:06:25,750 --> 00:06:27,650
Nothing, they can't fall asleep.

121
00:06:27,790 --> 00:06:28,710
Did you find Mom?

122
00:06:28,710 --> 00:06:31,250
Yes, she's in the hospital, but she'll be fine.

123
00:06:31,550 --> 00:06:32,550
It was the appendix.

124
00:06:33,750 --> 00:06:35,250
You went to the eye doctor for it?

125
00:06:35,750 --> 00:06:37,250
The appendix is a body part, Lexa.

126
00:06:37,270 --> 00:06:38,010
Shut up, you goose.

127
00:06:38,730 --> 00:06:39,390
Don't call her names.

128
00:06:39,570 --> 00:06:40,550
She just said I'm a body part.

129
00:06:40,770 --> 00:06:42,510
She said the appendix is a body part, Lexa.

130
00:06:42,950 --> 00:06:43,950
You too?

131
00:06:44,250 --> 00:06:45,150
Enough.

132
00:06:46,250 --> 00:06:48,450
From now on you two listen to me.

133
00:06:49,150 --> 00:06:50,050
So, home and sleep.

134
00:06:50,250 --> 00:06:53,150
You too. In the morning we'll sit down and figure out what's next.

135
00:06:53,750 --> 00:06:54,850
Can you handle it?

136
00:06:55,150 --> 00:06:56,750
I can handle even bed bugs.

137
00:06:57,650 --> 00:07:00,270
But Mr. Pacovsky, tomorrow there's no breakfast.

138
00:07:00,550 --> 00:07:01,950
Tomorrow is a weekday.

139
00:07:03,950 --> 00:07:05,150
As an exception then.

140
00:07:05,810 --> 00:07:06,390
Awesome.

141
00:07:07,750 --> 00:07:08,250
Good night.

142
00:07:13,850 --> 00:07:14,750
Well, good night.

143
00:07:14,750 --> 00:07:15,650
Good?

144
00:07:15,950 --> 00:07:18,330
Ozzak has a kilo of hot peppers in his belly, he's dreaming he's on fire.

145
00:07:18,550 --> 00:07:19,430
He screams in his sleep?

146
00:07:19,550 --> 00:07:21,550
No, he puts out fires in his sleep.

147
00:07:39,420 --> 00:07:40,300
Good morning.

148
00:07:40,640 --> 00:07:41,220
Morning.

149
00:07:41,450 --> 00:07:42,950
Oh, you're already here.

150
00:07:43,250 --> 00:07:44,250
Since five.

151
00:07:44,250 --> 00:07:46,850
What, they woke you up?

152
00:07:46,850 --> 00:07:47,270
No.

153
00:07:48,060 --> 00:07:49,540
Ozzak finished putting out fires at four thirty.

154
00:07:49,840 --> 00:07:51,800
But when we came, the shirt was just smoldering.

155
00:07:52,480 --> 00:07:54,300
So why were you here so early?

156
00:07:54,660 --> 00:07:57,280
Because we didn't know you don't eat breakfast until you wake up.

157
00:07:58,250 --> 00:07:59,540
When do you normally eat breakfast?

158
00:07:59,750 --> 00:08:04,240
When Mom comes home from work, we have breakfast together, she goes to sleep, and then our daily program starts.

159
00:08:04,350 --> 00:08:08,650
Usually we wait until dawn so we can see to string the beads.

160
00:08:08,950 --> 00:08:10,050
Electricity isn't free.

161
00:08:11,250 --> 00:08:12,430
Bon appetit.

162
00:08:12,550 --> 00:08:13,650
Bon appetit.

163
00:08:15,950 --> 00:08:17,850
Ow, what kind of tea is this?

164
00:08:18,350 --> 00:08:19,350
It's hot.

165
00:08:19,850 --> 00:08:20,750
Not the tea.

166
00:08:21,450 --> 00:08:22,650
It's kind of dirty.

167
00:08:23,480 --> 00:08:25,920
What's that brown tea called?

168
00:08:26,580 --> 00:08:28,420
Black, that's black tea.

169
00:08:28,560 --> 00:08:29,020
Oh.

170
00:08:30,450 --> 00:08:35,450
Could I get the cold clear kind that Mom gives us?

171
00:08:35,550 --> 00:08:37,850
Stop it, blow on it and eat.

172
00:08:38,250 --> 00:08:38,820
For next time.

173
00:08:39,150 --> 00:08:42,850
At our place, breakfast is at seven thirty, dinner is between six and seven.

174
00:08:42,980 --> 00:08:44,540
When do you normally go to bed?

175
00:08:44,840 --> 00:08:46,880
When it gets dark, because you can't see the beads anymore.

176
00:08:47,260 --> 00:08:49,800
But we can still watch the moon before bed.

177
00:08:49,860 --> 00:08:53,160
Yeah, but you got the moon banned for 14 days for that chemistry ball thing.

178
00:08:54,650 --> 00:08:56,350
It's waning anyway.

179
00:08:56,750 --> 00:09:03,850
So here's the deal, bedtime is 10 PM, and if you want, you can watch TV at our place before that.

180
00:09:04,650 --> 00:09:06,280
Oh wow, sis!

181
00:09:06,550 --> 00:09:10,350
But I've just gotten into watching the moon.

182
00:09:10,800 --> 00:09:13,450
What did I do to deserve this?

183
00:09:14,110 --> 00:09:14,830
Why are you crying?

184
00:09:14,690 --> 00:09:17,390
For God's sake, Simona didn't give the blue envelope to your dad.

185
00:09:17,470 --> 00:09:18,370
Or grandma.

186
00:09:18,690 --> 00:09:20,790
He already paints at grandma's a lot.

187
00:09:20,970 --> 00:09:23,770
And Dad, whenever he could watch us, he's on a polar expedition.

188
00:09:24,850 --> 00:09:25,930
Tough luck, right?

189
00:09:45,250 --> 00:09:46,350
Sorry I'm late.

190
00:09:46,750 --> 00:09:51,550
I went to the health insurance office to ask how much you can get for insurance fraud.

191
00:09:52,450 --> 00:09:53,570
More than for murder?

192
00:09:53,950 --> 00:09:55,350
Why do you ask?

193
00:09:55,750 --> 00:09:59,850
Because Simona is in the hospital with appendicitis under someone else's ID number.

194
00:10:00,250 --> 00:10:01,830
Oh my.

195
00:10:02,350 --> 00:10:02,950
Although...

196
00:10:03,250 --> 00:10:05,260
Actually, in her situation it makes sense.

197
00:10:05,260 --> 00:10:07,540
And what about my situation, doesn't that matter?

198
00:10:07,660 --> 00:10:09,220
Iva is covered by the state after all.

199
00:10:09,950 --> 00:10:11,650
Fine, but it's still fraud.

200
00:10:12,450 --> 00:10:13,650
Shouldn't I report it?

201
00:10:13,850 --> 00:10:16,650
The insurance company even has a bonus program for that.

202
00:10:17,150 --> 00:10:18,990
A bonus program, surely.

203
00:10:19,450 --> 00:10:20,670
Yes, a bonus program.

204
00:10:20,950 --> 00:10:23,850
For every report you get a multivitamin and some chips.

205
00:10:24,350 --> 00:10:26,350
But Simona is your friend.

206
00:10:26,550 --> 00:10:29,250
She's just used to getting away with everything.

207
00:10:29,750 --> 00:10:31,450
But I'm not helping her with this.

208
00:10:32,350 --> 00:10:34,650
And who pushed her in a wheelchair to social services when she applied for disability?

209
00:10:36,570 --> 00:10:38,490
She told me she had a sprained ankle.

210
00:10:38,530 --> 00:10:42,730
And who got her a Castle Guard uniform when she wanted a half-price tram pass?

211
00:10:43,290 --> 00:10:46,210
Fine, I stupidly fell for the story that she was going to a costume party.

212
00:10:46,290 --> 00:10:47,270
But that's over now.

213
00:10:47,650 --> 00:10:50,550
Tomas, you're doing this for yourself too.

214
00:10:51,450 --> 00:10:52,450
How for myself?

215
00:10:52,450 --> 00:10:54,950
What if they found out and locked Simona up?

216
00:10:55,850 --> 00:10:56,750
What about the kids?

217
00:10:57,580 --> 00:10:57,980
Right.

218
00:10:59,950 --> 00:11:02,550
They'd bring me the red letter.

219
00:11:13,670 --> 00:11:14,310
Exactly.

220
00:11:16,350 --> 00:11:18,650
Irma, the guests are coming.

221
00:11:19,950 --> 00:11:21,880
Welcome, your honor.

222
00:11:21,880 --> 00:11:22,380
Howdy.

223
00:11:22,950 --> 00:11:23,950
You've got someone here?

224
00:11:24,850 --> 00:11:25,750
No, that's marketing.

225
00:11:27,380 --> 00:11:28,020
Who?

226
00:11:29,550 --> 00:11:32,650
A little trick so it doesn't look like an abandoned bar.

227
00:11:32,650 --> 00:11:35,310
What'll you have?

228
00:11:35,550 --> 00:11:37,450
A beer, but it should've been here already.

229
00:11:40,150 --> 00:11:43,250
Radanka, the guests are complaining.

230
00:11:43,950 --> 00:11:46,050
Excuse me, one moment.

231
00:11:47,550 --> 00:11:50,850
Wait, wait, wait, she always marks it down only when she brings me the beer.

232
00:11:51,050 --> 00:11:52,450
That's so we don't forget.

233
00:11:54,120 --> 00:11:58,700
Right, it's pouring and here it is.

234
00:11:59,260 --> 00:12:00,600
There you go.

235
00:12:01,460 --> 00:12:02,580
It's not a full pint.

236
00:12:03,450 --> 00:12:05,200
It's a Slovak pint, it's smaller.

237
00:12:05,350 --> 00:12:06,050
Why?

238
00:12:06,450 --> 00:12:07,550
Smaller country, smaller pint.

239
00:12:09,160 --> 00:12:09,700
I see.

240
00:12:11,240 --> 00:12:12,720
You're making another tally mark?

241
00:12:13,100 --> 00:12:14,540
Well, you told me to yourself.

242
00:12:15,500 --> 00:12:16,360
Oh, right.

243
00:12:18,050 --> 00:12:18,560
Cheers.

244
00:12:18,850 --> 00:12:19,800
Cheers to you too.

245
00:12:29,950 --> 00:12:31,670
Damn it, I said six thirty, didn't I?

246
00:12:32,250 --> 00:12:33,470
I'll go get him.

247
00:12:33,470 --> 00:12:35,550
Good evening.

248
00:12:37,150 --> 00:12:37,620
Good evening.

249
00:12:37,950 --> 00:12:38,960
So where are you?

250
00:12:39,150 --> 00:12:40,450
We're waiting for you with dinner.

251
00:12:41,150 --> 00:12:43,500
Great, there's dinner, even though it's usually every other day.

252
00:12:45,650 --> 00:12:51,550
Sorry, Mr. Pacovsky, we'd rather save tonight's dinner for tomorrow so we don't go hungry at the end of the week.

253
00:12:52,330 --> 00:12:53,330
What do you mean, hungry.

254
00:12:53,330 --> 00:12:58,390
Well, for a week we get three breakfasts and three dinners, so we shouldn't use them all now.

255
00:12:58,390 --> 00:13:00,850
What do you mean three breakfasts, three dinners?

256
00:13:01,550 --> 00:13:02,610
What about lunch?

257
00:13:02,610 --> 00:13:03,650
That's on Sundays.

258
00:13:03,790 --> 00:13:04,310
Good Lord.

259
00:13:05,950 --> 00:13:07,290
Stop that and come eat.

260
00:13:10,350 --> 00:13:11,480
Lexa, quit fooling around and come.

261
00:13:11,480 --> 00:13:12,680
I'll smack you on Friday for this.

262
00:13:12,820 --> 00:13:14,760
And Saturday there's a sausage tasting at Harenda.

263
00:13:18,150 --> 00:13:19,840
Good evening.

264
00:13:20,250 --> 00:13:22,350
Here we are. What are you doing here so early?

265
00:13:22,450 --> 00:13:26,650
Bro, Simona is Simona, but Horvat...

266
00:13:26,810 --> 00:13:28,530
That guy really knows how to run a place.

267
00:13:28,530 --> 00:13:35,350
Imagine, he pours so fast that you drink 40 beers in the time you'd normally do 20, and he even walks you home.

268
00:13:35,950 --> 00:13:38,150
You drank 40 beers?

269
00:13:38,350 --> 00:13:40,050
Yeah, and I'm not even wasted.

270
00:13:40,070 --> 00:13:40,550
Really.

271
00:13:40,550 --> 00:13:42,910
So with your dad, is there some limit?

272
00:13:42,910 --> 00:13:44,270
What limit?

273
00:13:45,010 --> 00:13:46,210
When he's thirsty, let him drink.

274
00:13:46,270 --> 00:13:47,350
He's a bartender, right?

275
00:13:47,430 --> 00:13:48,290
A gem.

276
00:13:48,750 --> 00:13:51,990
But I have a deal with Simona that the limit is 15.

277
00:13:51,990 --> 00:13:52,570
Right.

278
00:13:52,950 --> 00:13:54,350
That comes to just...

279
00:13:54,950 --> 00:13:57,250
14,150.

280
00:13:57,850 --> 00:14:01,090
15 beers, for God's sake, not fourteen hundred.

281
00:14:01,450 --> 00:14:03,130
That's what you say.

282
00:14:04,950 --> 00:14:06,250
I gave you a discount.

283
00:14:07,850 --> 00:14:09,750
Beer for 35 crowns?

284
00:14:10,450 --> 00:14:11,350
Where's the discount?

285
00:14:11,550 --> 00:14:13,090
Every fiftieth one is free.

286
00:14:13,530 --> 00:14:15,530
But he only drank forty.

287
00:14:17,450 --> 00:14:20,350
Tomorrow he'll have to try harder.

288
00:14:21,460 --> 00:14:23,340
Sure, bro, relax, I can do it.

289
00:14:23,420 --> 00:14:25,260
But just in case, I'll have a few more hot peppers.

290
00:14:29,430 --> 00:14:30,270
Bon appetit.

291
00:14:38,850 --> 00:14:40,530
Simona, we need to talk.

292
00:14:40,530 --> 00:14:40,850
What?

293
00:14:41,510 --> 00:14:43,910
Is that how you look?

294
00:14:44,050 --> 00:14:44,730
Just in case.

295
00:14:44,770 --> 00:14:46,490
So they believe I'm sixteen.

296
00:14:47,310 --> 00:14:48,470
You look like a clown.

297
00:14:48,950 --> 00:14:51,710
Jesus, you're so behind the times, this is what people wear now.

298
00:14:51,710 --> 00:14:52,370
Give me a break.

299
00:14:52,950 --> 00:14:55,550
I'm acting, in case someone walks by.

300
00:14:55,750 --> 00:14:57,470
God, what if they see through you?

301
00:14:57,470 --> 00:14:58,010
Relax.

302
00:14:58,450 --> 00:15:03,490
I got stuffed animals, I cry a lot, I always have my phone, and I don't eat rolls so I don't get fat.

303
00:15:03,490 --> 00:15:05,150
And I'm also learning the right words.

304
00:15:05,450 --> 00:15:07,850
Here, ask me how school was.

305
00:15:09,110 --> 00:15:10,090
How was school?

306
00:15:10,710 --> 00:15:11,110
Lit!

307
00:15:12,810 --> 00:15:14,410
Thank God Iva doesn't talk like that.

308
00:15:14,530 --> 00:15:17,130
Good thing I'm here, they'd never believe it from her.

309
00:15:17,330 --> 00:15:18,050
What do you want?

310
00:15:18,790 --> 00:15:20,230
You should talk to Horvat.

311
00:15:20,750 --> 00:15:23,150
I'm not speaking to Horvat.

312
00:15:23,850 --> 00:15:24,850
He's not keeping the limit.

313
00:15:25,150 --> 00:15:27,550
Ozzak cost me just today what he normally does in a week.

314
00:15:27,850 --> 00:15:29,250
So you'll talk to him?

315
00:15:30,110 --> 00:15:30,510
Lit.

316
00:15:32,350 --> 00:15:34,050
Even though I don't know what that means.

317
00:15:34,120 --> 00:15:35,140
You're a fossil.

318
00:15:35,320 --> 00:15:36,280
Like, yeah?

319
00:15:36,900 --> 00:15:38,040
Just say it normally.

320
00:15:38,240 --> 00:15:38,620
Fine.

321
00:15:39,050 --> 00:15:39,920
I'll talk to him.

322
00:15:39,920 --> 00:15:41,040
He's supposed to stop by anyway.

323
00:15:41,140 --> 00:15:41,540
Thanks.

324
00:15:44,960 --> 00:15:45,920
Are you the father?

325
00:15:45,920 --> 00:15:47,980
Yes, Pacovsky.

326
00:15:48,250 --> 00:15:51,760
Then tell your daughter to return those toys to pediatric oncology.

327
00:15:51,760 --> 00:15:52,600
Well, Iva...

328
00:15:53,590 --> 00:15:54,670
Iva!

329
00:15:55,130 --> 00:15:55,690
What?

330
00:16:06,090 --> 00:16:10,530
Sis, sis, look, they're replaying that ad about the laundry detergent that works better than the other one.

331
00:16:11,070 --> 00:16:12,250
Don't bother me, I'm growing.

332
00:16:13,030 --> 00:16:14,710
Are there still bed bugs at your place?

333
00:16:15,250 --> 00:16:17,070
Just Zanetka and Ivanka.

334
00:16:17,070 --> 00:16:19,250
Virka and Johanka went off somewhere.

335
00:16:20,150 --> 00:16:21,450
You gave them names?

336
00:16:22,350 --> 00:16:24,010
Everyone names their pet.

337
00:16:24,350 --> 00:16:25,830
How else would I call them?

338
00:16:26,150 --> 00:16:27,550
How do you call bed bugs?

339
00:16:27,570 --> 00:16:27,790
Well.

340
00:16:28,650 --> 00:16:31,090
Zanetka, Ivanka.

341
00:16:31,090 --> 00:16:31,730
Like that?

342
00:16:33,150 --> 00:16:34,400
And do they actually come?

343
00:16:34,400 --> 00:16:34,920
No.

344
00:16:34,920 --> 00:16:36,850
Want to go see them?

345
00:16:37,000 --> 00:16:37,300
No.

346
00:16:37,300 --> 00:16:39,550
Then why did you ask about them?

347
00:16:40,250 --> 00:16:42,710
I wanted to hide from Lexa at your place.

348
00:16:43,150 --> 00:16:47,550
But if Zanetka and Ivanka are still there, I'll stay here for a bit.

349
00:16:48,580 --> 00:16:50,680
Hey, they're showing something with instant soup.

350
00:16:50,820 --> 00:16:52,520
That's definitely about astronauts.

351
00:16:55,950 --> 00:16:57,450
About time you showed up.

352
00:16:58,250 --> 00:16:58,950
Lit.

353
00:16:59,850 --> 00:17:00,350
Dad.

354
00:17:01,150 --> 00:17:03,050
What, don't you young people talk like this?

355
00:17:03,070 --> 00:17:04,890
Yeah, but you don't talk like that.

356
00:17:05,010 --> 00:17:06,130
I'm a fossil after all.

357
00:17:06,410 --> 00:17:07,750
You didn't hear me.

358
00:17:07,810 --> 00:17:08,970
Don't talk like that.

359
00:17:09,070 --> 00:17:09,610
Okay, okay.

360
00:17:11,050 --> 00:17:12,350
Did you talk to Mom?

361
00:17:12,510 --> 00:17:13,010
Yeah.

362
00:17:13,650 --> 00:17:14,550
Is she feeling better?

363
00:17:15,540 --> 00:17:17,000
She's totally rejuvenated there.

364
00:17:18,060 --> 00:17:18,560
Lit.

365
00:17:24,750 --> 00:17:27,350
Hello, could you please connect me to surgery?

366
00:17:27,450 --> 00:17:27,950
Thank you.

367
00:17:30,490 --> 00:17:30,990
Hello.

368
00:17:32,950 --> 00:17:33,910
Yo, it's Tom.

369
00:17:35,750 --> 00:17:37,850
I'm calling about Iva Pacovska.

370
00:17:39,750 --> 00:17:43,720
Yeah, we go to the same school.

371
00:17:43,720 --> 00:17:44,900
Tomas, what are you doing?

372
00:17:45,400 --> 00:17:45,900
One sec.

373
00:17:47,050 --> 00:17:51,250
I'm calling the hospital asking about Simona as her teenage friend, so they believe she's 16.

374
00:17:53,420 --> 00:17:56,220
Give it here, anyone can tell you're a total fossil.

375
00:17:58,210 --> 00:17:59,990
How do you know their slang?

376
00:18:00,170 --> 00:18:01,770
I ride the tram sometimes, check it.

377
00:18:04,050 --> 00:18:06,150
Yo, this is Maca, I wanna ask.

378
00:18:06,150 --> 00:18:08,550
How much longer is Iva gonna be at your place?

379
00:18:09,550 --> 00:18:13,250
Don't give me grief, her old man will give me the number.

380
00:18:13,950 --> 00:18:14,850
Today, yeah?

381
00:18:16,450 --> 00:18:17,550
Wicked gnarly.

382
00:18:18,650 --> 00:18:20,860
Sweet, I'll give her fossil the heads-up.

383
00:18:20,860 --> 00:18:21,500
Peace out.

384
00:18:25,150 --> 00:18:26,080
Well, Marcelka.

385
00:18:26,250 --> 00:18:27,780
I was brutally strict, wasn't I?

386
00:18:27,780 --> 00:18:28,480
Yes you were.

387
00:18:29,300 --> 00:18:32,440
Now they won't suspect her, and she's going home right after rounds anyway.

388
00:18:32,600 --> 00:18:33,400
I'm off then.

389
00:18:33,420 --> 00:18:34,560
You'll manage here alone.

390
00:18:34,680 --> 00:18:34,880
Sure.

391
00:18:36,470 --> 00:18:36,910
Lit.

392
00:18:46,990 --> 00:18:47,930
Hurry up!

393
00:18:48,050 --> 00:18:50,930
The instructions from Simona are written in pencil on a napkin.

394
00:18:50,970 --> 00:18:52,470
You can't read them.

395
00:18:53,550 --> 00:18:57,010
Pour beer when he's on the steps.

396
00:18:57,950 --> 00:18:59,950
And what would beer be doing on the steps?

397
00:19:00,450 --> 00:19:02,450
When I'm on the steps.

398
00:19:03,580 --> 00:19:04,220
Me?

399
00:19:05,450 --> 00:19:06,740
So go to the steps.

400
00:19:06,850 --> 00:19:08,360
There, hop to it and pour.

401
00:19:08,360 --> 00:19:12,690
And today I want a Czech measure.

402
00:19:12,930 --> 00:19:13,810
Sure thing.

403
00:19:14,550 --> 00:19:16,750
I have that written down too.

404
00:19:19,550 --> 00:19:21,250
That's what it should look like.

405
00:19:24,650 --> 00:19:26,200
Why are you so grumpy?

406
00:19:26,550 --> 00:19:27,640
Because I'm bored!

407
00:19:27,950 --> 00:19:29,960
Doing everything exactly as it's written.

408
00:19:29,960 --> 00:19:31,960
Anything creative is forbidden.

409
00:19:31,960 --> 00:19:35,850
Making extra tally marks, pouring under measure, watering down the beer.

410
00:19:36,350 --> 00:19:37,950
That's like slave labor!

411
00:19:38,950 --> 00:19:40,140
I actually understand you.

412
00:19:40,650 --> 00:19:44,050
With a donkey like you, you could really get things done.

413
00:19:44,550 --> 00:19:49,740
But all I'm allowed to do is make tally marks until there are 15.

414
00:19:51,350 --> 00:19:54,350
You know what, just write fifteen right away and let's start drinking.

415
00:19:56,850 --> 00:19:59,750
Maybe, you're not such a donkey after all.

416
00:20:29,750 --> 00:20:31,150
They had breakfast too.

417
00:20:31,750 --> 00:20:32,410
What do you mean?

418
00:20:33,050 --> 00:20:34,810
Breakfast and dinner in the same day?

419
00:20:35,050 --> 00:20:36,250
So you've spoiled them.

420
00:20:36,750 --> 00:20:39,250
Look Simona, I don't want to discuss your parenting.

421
00:20:39,650 --> 00:20:41,710
But I don't think staying with us hurt them.

422
00:20:41,950 --> 00:20:42,850
Quite the opposite.

423
00:20:43,750 --> 00:20:47,250
Yesterday for example, Sasa learned to shower with the lights on.

424
00:20:48,790 --> 00:20:49,230
Are you crazy?

425
00:20:49,850 --> 00:20:51,450
Is electricity free?

426
00:20:51,950 --> 00:20:53,630
Plus, yesterday it was Lexa's turn to shower.

427
00:20:53,630 --> 00:20:54,430
He took a bath.

428
00:20:55,070 --> 00:20:55,510
What?

429
00:20:56,680 --> 00:20:59,180
I step out for a moment and you turn my kids into Rockefellers.

430
00:20:59,360 --> 00:21:00,060
Come on.

431
00:21:00,260 --> 00:21:01,020
Come on what?

432
00:21:01,140 --> 00:21:02,940
You might as well have given them an allowance.

433
00:21:03,220 --> 00:21:04,080
I did.

434
00:21:04,660 --> 00:21:05,920
But only two hundred.

435
00:21:07,550 --> 00:21:09,340
They spent two hundred crowns?

436
00:21:09,650 --> 00:21:10,950
No, definitely not.

437
00:21:11,150 --> 00:21:16,250
Sasa immediately put the two-hundred note in a frame, and the super saw Lexa burying something in the garden.

438
00:21:18,250 --> 00:21:19,850
Wait till you're the one in the hospital.

439
00:21:20,150 --> 00:21:22,450
You think I'd leave Iva in your care?

440
00:21:22,450 --> 00:21:23,070
Who else then?

441
00:21:23,430 --> 00:21:23,830
Ozzak?

442
00:21:24,750 --> 00:21:26,090
Wait, I'll get you back for this.

443
00:21:26,090 --> 00:21:26,690
How?

444
00:21:29,650 --> 00:21:31,190
I'll let Iva have a party at your place.

445
00:21:31,650 --> 00:21:32,350
With bowling pins.

446
00:21:32,450 --> 00:21:33,750
And alcohol.

447
00:21:34,240 --> 00:21:34,760
Hard liquor.

448
00:21:45,560 --> 00:21:46,080
Horvat?

449
00:21:47,830 --> 00:21:48,350
Simona!

450
00:21:49,550 --> 00:21:50,530
You're back already?

451
00:21:50,850 --> 00:21:51,910
As you can see.

452
00:21:51,910 --> 00:21:53,670
Have a beer, tonight it's on Horvat.

453
00:21:54,270 --> 00:21:54,790
Horvat?

454
00:21:57,250 --> 00:21:58,550
15 tally marks.

455
00:22:01,050 --> 00:22:02,700
30 beers short.

456
00:22:02,700 --> 00:22:05,920
We had this promotion to bring in customers.

457
00:22:06,020 --> 00:22:07,220
I can see business is booming.

458
00:22:07,360 --> 00:22:08,640
They'll bring me customers.

459
00:22:08,860 --> 00:22:09,940
You drank them?

460
00:22:10,140 --> 00:22:11,540
We already drank them.

461
00:22:12,600 --> 00:22:14,340
You're paying for that keg.

462
00:22:14,760 --> 00:22:17,280
No, Simona, it's marketing.

463
00:22:19,850 --> 00:22:22,350
If you don't bring money by tomorrow, I'll show you marketing.

464
00:22:23,830 --> 00:22:24,210
And get out!

465
00:22:24,850 --> 00:22:26,250
Can you believe this?

466
00:22:27,050 --> 00:22:27,550
So...

467
00:22:27,650 --> 00:22:33,250
Simona, I'm taking care of the pub for you while you're lounging around hospitals.

468
00:22:33,350 --> 00:22:36,050
I could break my arms and legs and this is what I get?

469
00:22:38,340 --> 00:22:38,860
Bye.

470
00:22:38,900 --> 00:22:39,340
Hello.

471
00:22:42,260 --> 00:22:42,780
Bro.

472
00:22:43,750 --> 00:22:45,210
How's it going?

473
00:22:45,210 --> 00:22:46,590
It's four in the afternoon.

474
00:22:46,810 --> 00:22:48,530
Yeah, and we've got this promotion going.

475
00:22:49,490 --> 00:22:51,370
You'll have a promotion tomorrow at the store.

476
00:22:52,250 --> 00:22:54,870
I make fifteen tally marks and slack off the rest of the time?

477
00:22:54,870 --> 00:22:55,390
No.

478
00:22:56,150 --> 00:22:59,100
Marcelka will mark a tally for every crate you unload.

479
00:22:59,100 --> 00:23:00,320
And there are at least thirty.

480
00:23:01,150 --> 00:23:02,350
Ooh, even more.

481
00:23:05,650 --> 00:23:06,170
Mommy!

482
00:23:06,250 --> 00:23:06,630
Mom!

483
00:23:07,330 --> 00:23:08,210
Hey, hey, hey.

484
00:23:08,800 --> 00:23:10,580
We bought this for you from our allowance.

485
00:23:13,750 --> 00:23:14,530
Nice flowers.

486
00:23:15,250 --> 00:23:15,770
Thanks.

487
00:23:16,450 --> 00:23:17,150
Do you have the receipt?

488
00:23:17,350 --> 00:23:18,130
Yes, we do.

489
00:23:18,130 --> 00:23:18,650
Good.

490
00:23:20,450 --> 00:23:23,140
Mom, guess what, at the Pacovskys' they eat every day.

491
00:23:23,550 --> 00:23:26,350
And in the bathroom they can even turn the red faucet.

492
00:23:29,210 --> 00:23:29,730
Like this.

493
00:23:31,050 --> 00:23:33,690
The Pacovskys are a peculiar family.

494
00:23:34,150 --> 00:23:42,450
But at our place, like everywhere else, there are breakfast days and dinner days, and the red faucet releases gas.

495
00:23:43,020 --> 00:23:44,560
You don't want to blow up, do you?

496
00:23:44,760 --> 00:23:45,300
No.

497
00:23:47,250 --> 00:23:49,850
But their water was so nicely warm.

498
00:23:50,750 --> 00:23:52,180
Warm water gives you pneumonia.

499
00:23:52,650 --> 00:23:53,250
You sure forgot fast how good we have it together.

500
00:23:56,040 --> 00:23:57,120
We haven't forgotten, Mom.

501
00:23:57,180 --> 00:23:58,360
We're happiest with you.

502
00:23:59,450 --> 00:24:00,950
You're trying awfully hard.

503
00:24:01,150 --> 00:24:03,050
Some bugs must have escaped again, huh?

504
00:24:03,250 --> 00:24:07,350
I caught them all already, only Zanetka was left and I'll catch her too.

505
00:24:07,850 --> 00:24:08,650
Alright.

506
00:24:09,350 --> 00:24:10,150
And you, Lexa?

507
00:24:10,350 --> 00:24:11,840
No homeless people?

508
00:24:12,150 --> 00:24:12,840
No, Mom.

509
00:24:12,840 --> 00:24:14,540
Yeah right, you wanted to bring one home.

510
00:24:14,680 --> 00:24:15,360
But I didn't.

511
00:24:15,460 --> 00:24:16,300
He smelled too bad.

512
00:24:16,680 --> 00:24:17,500
Good, Lexa.

513
00:24:18,450 --> 00:24:20,500
You don't still have the moon ban, do you?

514
00:24:20,750 --> 00:24:22,250
Yeah, ten more days.

515
00:24:23,050 --> 00:24:24,150
I'm lifting it.

516
00:24:24,450 --> 00:24:25,450
You can look at it.

517
00:24:25,750 --> 00:24:27,620
Awesome, it's already growing back.

518
00:24:28,750 --> 00:24:31,850
I don't think the moon grows, it's not a plant.

519
00:24:32,130 --> 00:24:32,730
Oh right.

520
00:24:34,350 --> 00:24:34,910
Dad.

521
00:24:34,910 --> 00:24:35,510
Yeah?

522
00:24:36,450 --> 00:24:40,850
If you ever have to go to the hospital, send me to an orphanage instead.

523
00:24:41,550 --> 00:24:42,650
You can count on it.

524
00:25:13,450 --> 00:25:15,550
You thought I wouldn't find you, huh?
